docs.snippet: Foreign exchanges showed more reserve in their movement and business last week than previously. The reduction in the "short" interest in the French franc which had been an influence in lifting that bill following Premier-Designate Blum's opposition...
docs.lead_paragraph: Foreign exchanges showed more reserve in their movement and business last week than previously. The reduction in the "short" interest in the French franc which had been an influence in lifting that bill following Premier-Designate Blum's opposition to devaluation was a factor, coupled with the holiday on Thursday, in limiting business and fluctuations.

docs.lead_paragraph: A rise in the pound sterling to the highest since early February, weakness in the French franc and the gold bloc as a result of which engagements of gold abroad aggregated $39,943,000, and an advance in the Dutch Bank rate represented the budget of interesting events in the foreign exchange market last week.
